g/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Novak Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 493, \"end\": 505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rafael Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Djokovic's 31st win in a rivalry which began on the same Roland Garros clay courts in 2006.\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 725, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 634, \"end\": 642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.890238373301731e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 691, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0314487359304327e-16, \"text\": \"Roland Garros\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Open\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The clash on July 29 was their first meeting in over two years after Nadal's various struggles with injury.\", \"from\": 727, \"to\": 834, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 796, \"end\": 801, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal was largely outclassed in the much anticipated encounter, only coming briefly to life when he won four games in a row in the second set.\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 978, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 836, \"end\": 841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very relieved.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1000, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everything was going my way, I was 6-1, 4-0 up, but I played a sloppy service game and gave him chances,\\\" said Djokovic, who added: \\\"I never thought in 2006 that we'd still be playing each other almost 20 years later.\\\"\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1112, \"end\": 1120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.890238373301731e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal, meanwhile, said he will make a decision on his future \\\"after the Olympics\\\".\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1303, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"When this tournament is over, I will take the necessary decisions based on my feelings and sensations.\\\"\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a sign of the wear and tear the pair have endured in recent months, Djokovic wore a protective strapping around his right knee while Nadal's right thigh was heavily strapped.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1596, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1490, \"end\": 1498, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.890238373301731e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}, {\"begin\": 1555, \"end\": 1560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the 37-year-old played freely, forcing Nadal to scamper around Court Philippe Chatrier, where the Spaniard had collected 14 of his 22 Grand Slam titles.\", \"from\": 1598, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 1665, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Court Philippe Chatrier\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\"}, {\"begin\": 1665, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Court Philippe Chatrier\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\"}, {\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"score\": 0.6840717625726255, \"rank\": 0.4616876441691984, \"text\": \"Spaniard\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spaniards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Serb raced to a 4-0 lead on the back of a double break and held for 5-0 before Nadal stopped the rot, much to the relief of the  packed crowd.\", \"from\": 1756, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1760, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9519214689344327, \"rank\": 0.050253020451899694, \"text\": \"Serb\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}, {\"begin\": 1839, \"end\": 1844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic pocketed the one-sided opener when 2008 Olympic singles gold medallist Nadal ballooned a forehand wide of the mark.\", \"from\": 1904, \"to\": 2028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1984, \"end\": 1989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statistics made grim reading for the 38-year-old, who managed to eke out just four points off Djokovic's serve in the first set.\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2162, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2128, \"end\": 2136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.890238373301731e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was no respite for Nadal, playing just his seventh tournament of an injury-plagued season, as Djokovic again carved out a double break for a 4-0 lead in the second set.\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2189, \"end\": 2194, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 2264, \"end\": 2272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.890238373301731e-21, \"text\": \"Djokovic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Novak_Djokovic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic, seeking a first Olympic gold medal to add to his 24 Grand Slam singles titles, surprisingly handed Nadal a lifeline when he served up a double fault to be broken for the first time.\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2448, \"end\": 2453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nadal retrieved the second break to claw his way back from 0-4 to 4-4 as the top seed suddenly went off the boil.\", \"from\": 2532, \"to\": 2645, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Djokovic responded in style, a drop shot leaving Nadal flat-footed as the Serb broke for 5-4 on a fourth break point and clinched victory in style with an ace.\", \"from\": 2646, \"to\": 2805, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2720, \"end\": 2724, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.9519214689344327, \"rank\": 0.050253020451899694, \"text\": \"Serb\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He next faces either German Dominik Koepfer or Italy's Matteo Arnaldi in the third round.\", \"from\": 2807, \"to\": 2896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2828, \"end\": 2834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.8724777210377852, \"rank\": 0.14430896635319965, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2835, \"end\": 2850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominik_Koepfer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dominik Koepfer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominik_Koepfer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominik_Koepfer\"}, {\"begin\": 2854, \"end\": 2859, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999992355745428, \"rank\": 7.644250831909602e-07, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2862, \"end\": 2876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Arnaldi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Arnaldi\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Arnaldi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Arnaldi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite his defeat on July 29, Nadal still has hopes of a gold medal in the men's doubles, where he is playing alongside Carlos Alcaraz.\", \"from\": 2898, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2929, \"end\": 2934, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.375163158435965e-23, \"text\": \"Nadal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rafael_Nadal\"}, {\"begin\": 3019, \"end\": 3033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the women's draw, four-time French Open champion Iga Swiatek underlined her status as the heavy favourite for gold, swatting home hope Diane Parry aside 6-1, 6-1 in the earlier match on Court Philippe Chatrier.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3088, \"end\": 3091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.456937421682137e-15, \"text\": \"Iga\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Iga_Province\"}, {\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diane_Parry\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diane Parry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diane_Parry\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diane_Parry\"}, {\"begin\": 3225, \"end\": 3248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Court Philippe Chatrier\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_Roland_Garros\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Pole won the first five games of the match and broke five times as she strolled to victory in just 74 minutes.\", \"from\": 3251, \"to\": 3365, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Swiatek, who lost in the second round in Tokyo, will meet China's Wang Xiyu for a place in the quarter-finals.\", \"from\": 3366, \"to\": 3476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3407, \"end\": 3412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9999999998904059, \"rank\": 1.0968187144701703e-10, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 3424, \"end\": 3429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7073848992289022, \"rank\": 0.41336534534260433, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3432, \"end\": 3441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Xiyu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wang Xiyu\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Xiyu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wang_Xiyu\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world No.\", \"from\": 3478, \"to\": 3491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1 has won her last 23 matches at Roland Garros, with three clay-court titles already under her belt this season.\", \"from\": 3492, \"to\": 3604, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A day earlier on July 28, two-time singles gold medallist Andy Murray kept his Olympic dream - and career - alive for one more match at least after teaming up with fellow Briton Dan Evans to beat Japanese duo Kei Nishikori and Taro Daniel in a miraculous comeback.\", \"from\": 3606, \"to\": 3870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3664, \"end\": 3675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.992803053771807e-8